<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E802513E7EC1F9533D53F839" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE802513E7EC1F9533D53F839" blockId="2.[151,760,1671,2078]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7EC1F9533E4DF979" bold="true" box="[151,268,1671,1694]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male body length 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7F99F9533D2DF979" box="[463,620,1671,1694]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.16" metricValueMax="3.23" metricValueMin="3.09" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="3.16" valueMax="3.23" valueMin="3.09">3.09–3.23 mm</quantity>
. Antennomere 9 with broad depression in apical half, with disc-like impression inside depression; antennomeres 10 broadly depressed and antennomere 11 deeply concave on ventral side. Horn-like metaventral processes in lateral view elongate and bifurcate at apices. Protibia with short, blunt preapical projection; mesotrochanter with acute ventral spine. Median lobe of aedeagus asymmetric, narrowing apically; parameres broad at bases and narrowed in apical halves; endophallus with spine-like structures and one elongate sclerite. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E802513E7EC1F8333B6AFC12" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE802513E7EC1F8333B2BFC32" blockId="2.[151,760,1671,2078]" lastBlockId="2.[828,1437,190,1269]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7EC1F8333E1EF819" bold="true" box="[151,351,2023,2046]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
Description. 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7F71F8333E1EF819" bold="true" box="[295,351,2023,2046]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Male</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7F3AF8333EFEF819" box="[364,447,2023,2046]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[151,182,2057,2076]" captionTargetBox="[258,1324,1020,2034]" captionTargetId="figure-392@1.[255,1333,1017,2038]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Dorsal habitus of Labomimus males. A – L. cavicornis sp. nov.; B – L. cucphuong sp. nov. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037466/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7C0EF8333DB5F819" box="[600,756,2023,2046]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.16" metricValueMax="3.23" metricValueMin="3.09" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="3.16" valueMax="3.23" valueMin="3.09">3.09–3.23 mm</quantity>
. Head slightly broader than long, HL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7C75F7D33D81F7F9" box="[547,704,2055,2078]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.85" metricValueMax="6.1" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.585" valueMax="0.61" valueMin="0.56">0.56–0.61 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7D6AFF6A3C9AFF32" box="[828,987,190,213]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" metricValueMax="6.3" metricValueMin="5.8999999999999995" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.61" valueMax="0.63" valueMin="0.59">0.59–0.63 mm</quantity>
; eyes prominent, each composed of about 41 facets. Antennomeres 2–8 of similar shape, each moniliform; antennomeres 9–11 (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7A36FF2A3BF1FEF2" box="[1120,1200,254,277]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[221,1369,601,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-202@3.[218,1370,601,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cavicornis sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in lateroventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037470/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) forming distinct club; antennomere 9 with large depression in apical half, and one disc-like impression inside depression; antennomeres 10 broadly depressed and antennomeres 11 with broad and deep concavity on ventral side. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7B16FEAA3AD5FE72" box="[1344,1428,382,405]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[221,1369,601,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-202@3.[218,1370,601,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cavicornis sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in lateroventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037470/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as wide, PL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7AF7FE4A3BBEFE52" box="[1185,1279,414,437]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.56">0.56 mm</quantity>
, PW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7B65FE4A3C29FE32" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.75" metricValueMax="5.8999999999999995" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.575" valueMax="0.59" valueMin="0.56">0.56–0.59 mm</quantity>
, narrowed anteriorly at apical 2/5. Elytra broader than long, EL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7DF3FE0A3B07FE12" box="[933,1094,478,501]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.05" metricValueMax="9.399999999999999" metricValueMin="8.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.905" valueMax="0.94" valueMin="0.87">0.87–0.94 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7AD1FE0A3A66FE12" box="[1159,1319,478,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.13" metricValueMax="1.15" metricValueMin="1.11" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="1.13" valueMax="1.15" valueMin="1.11">1.11–1.15 mm</quantity>
. Horn-like metaventral processes (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7A6FFE2A3BCCFDF2" box="[1081,1165,510,533]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[221,1369,601,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-202@3.[218,1370,601,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cavicornis sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in lateroventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037470/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) in lateral view elongate and curved upward, bifurcate at apices. Protrochanter (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7B24FDCA3C1CFDB2" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[221,1369,601,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-202@3.[218,1370,601,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cavicornis sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in lateroventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037470/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) with tiny ventral tooth; profemur angularly expanded at middle; protibia (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7A4DFD8A3B31FD92" box="[1051,1136,606,629]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[221,1369,601,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-202@3.[218,1370,601,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cavicornis sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in lateroventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037470/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
) with blunt process before apex; mesotrochanter (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7A64FDAA3BC2FD72" box="[1074,1155,638,661]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[221,1369,601,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-202@3.[218,1370,601,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cavicornis sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in lateroventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037470/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
) with acute ventral spine; mesofemur (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7D96FD4A3B4EFD52" box="[960,1039,670,693]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[221,1369,601,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-202@3.[218,1370,601,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cavicornis sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in lateroventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037470/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
), metatrochanter and metafemur (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7B27FD4A3C1CFD32" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[221,1369,601,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-202@3.[218,1370,601,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cavicornis sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in lateroventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037470/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
) simple.Abdomen broad at base and narrowed apically, AL 1.00– 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7DF3FD0A3B4BFD12" box="[933,1034,734,757]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.02" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="1.02">1.02 mm</quantity>
, AW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7A1DFD0A3BADFD12" box="[1099,1260,734,757]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.155" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.11" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="1.155" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.11">1.11–1.20 mm</quantity>
. Sternite 7 (IX) (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7D12FD2A3CD9FCF2" box="[836,920,766,789]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[221,1369,601,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-202@3.[218,1370,601,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cavicornis sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in lateroventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037470/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
) hemi-membranous, elongately oval. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7D15FCCA3CF0FCD2" box="[835,945,798,821]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[221,1369,601,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-202@3.[218,1370,601,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cavicornis sp. nov.A – left antennal club, in lateroventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037470/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Figs 2I–E</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7D96FCCA3B5EFCD2" box="[960,1055,798,821]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.55">0.55 mm</quantity>
long; median lobe asymmetric dorso-ventrally, narrowing apically; parameres short, curved ventrally, broad at bases and abruptly narrowed for apical halves; endophallus comprising one large, elongate and curved sclerite, and numerous hemi-membranous spinelike structures at apical part.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE802513E7D0CFC0A3B6AFC12" blockId="2.[828,1437,190,1269]" box="[858,1067,990,1013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7D0CFC0A3CF5FC12" bold="true" box="[858,948,990,1013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7D0CFC0A3CECFC12" bold="true" box="[858,941,990,1013]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E802513E7D6AFC2A3B9FFBB2" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE802513E7D6AFC2A3B9FFBB2" blockId="2.[828,1437,190,1269]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7D6AFC2A3B60FBF2" bold="true" box="[828,1057,1022,1045]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
This is a very distinctive species which can be easily separated from all congeners by unique modification of the male antennal club.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E802513E7D6AFB8A3A30FB32" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE802513E7D6AFB8A3A30FB32" blockId="2.[828,1437,190,1269]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7D6AFB8A3CFBFB92" bold="true" box="[828,954,1118,1141]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is a Latin adjective composed of 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7D0CFBAA3CD6FB72" box="[858,919,1150,1173]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">cavus</emphasis>
(- 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7DE7FBAA3CFFFB72" box="[945,958,1150,1173]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">a</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7D80FBAA3CB6FB72" box="[982,1015,1150,1173]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">um</emphasis>
; meaning hollow, concave, excavated) and 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7D30FB4A3CE6FB52" box="[870,935,1182,1205]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">cornis</emphasis>
(- 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7DEBFB4A3C8FFB52" box="[957,974,1182,1205]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">is</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7DB4FB4A3CAFFB52" box="[994,1006,1182,1205]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">e</emphasis>
; meaning horned), referring to the strongly depressed and concave antennal clubs of the male.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E802513E7D6AFB0A3BEDFB12" box="[828,1196,1246,1269]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE802513E7D6AFB0A3BEDFB12" blockId="2.[828,1437,190,1269]" box="[828,1196,1246,1269]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7D6AFB0A3C8FFB12" bold="true" box="[828,974,1246,1269]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE802513E7D82FB0A3B72FB12" box="[980,1075,1246,1269]" name="Vietnam" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
: Đồng Nai.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
